<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td>
      <div align="center"><b><u>PART VI SPECIAL INSTRUCTIONS/GUIDELINES WITH REGARD 
        TOREVISED/NEW DOCUMENTS:</u></b></div>
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td>(The special instructions given in this Part are only supplemental to 
      the general guidelines on documentation contained in Chapter I and Part 
      I of this Chapter)</td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><b><u>1. Letter of Guarantee (SD-01):</u></b></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><p align="justify">This is in substitution of earlier S-1 deed. This is the guarantee letter 
      to be used for all guarantees excepting for Agricultural advances for which 
      another guarantee letter viz. SD-08 is prescribed. In page no. 1 name &amp; 
      address of the principal viz. the Borrower is to be written. Signature of 
      the guarantor/s should appear in all the pages and in the last page the 
      full name &amp; address of the guarantor/s is/ are to be written.</p></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><b><u>cxlvi) Pledge Agreement (SD-02):</u></b></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><p align="justify">This deed substitutes earlier S-2 Deed. This can be used for all advances 
      for which S-2 deed was used earlier, Viz. for creating charge over the movable 
      goods which are the security for Cash Credit (Pledge) facility.</p></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><b><u>3. Hypothecation (Goods) Agreement (SD-03):</u></b></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><p align="justify">This deed substitutes earlier S-3 Hypothecation Deed. This is a hypothecation 
      Deed for all advances for which S-3 was used earlier. Please note that for 
      agricultural advances, separate hypothecation Deed viz. SD-07 is to be used. 
      This deed may be used preferably where only Cash Credit (Hyp.) facility 
      against goods is sanctioned (and not multiple facilities)</p></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><b><u>4. Packing Credit Agreement (SD-04):</u></b></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><p align="justify">This deed is a revised version of the Packing Credit Agreement, viz. S-4A 
      presently in vogue and this substitutes S-4A. The revised version is made 
      in the form of a Hypothecation Agreement. There are two schedules in the 
      deed : One for Hypothecated goods and the other for rate of interest. The 
      same has to be carefully filled in, apart from other blanks in the documents.</p> 
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><b><u>5. Hypothecation ( Book Debts ) Agreement (SD-05):</u></b></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><p align="justify">This is a revised version of the Hypothecation of Book Debts Agreement 
      which was in vogue since long and is in use by some of the major urban branches. 
      This is meant for Cash Credit (Hypothecation) facility against Book debts.</p></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><b><u>6. Hypothecation Agreement of Goods &amp; Debts (SD-06):</u></b></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><p align="justify">This document is a revised version of composite Hypothecation Agreement 
      for stocks and book debts. This can be used for advances of Cash Credit 
      against both stock and Book Debts. This is a suitable document where multiple 
      facility of Cash Credit against Stock &amp; Book Debts is sanctioned.</p></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><b><u>7.Hypothecation Agreement (Agricultural Advances)(SD-07):</u></b></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><p align="justify">This is a common document for creation of hypothecation charge over all 
      movable securities in agricultural advances, viz. standing crops, agricultural 
      implements, boats, machines, herd, fish, silkworms etc. involved in agricultural 
      advances. This substitutes the AB-I agreement introduced vide Instruction 
      Circular No. 5926 dated 31-8-99.</p></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><b><u>cxlvii) Guarantee Deed (Agricultural Advances) (SD-08):</u></b></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><p align="justify">This is a new Deed of Guarantee for agricultural advances introduced vide 
      Instruction circular 5926 stated above. This is meant for only agricultural 
      advances.</p></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><b><u>cxlviii) Hypothecation (Consumer Goods) Agreement (SD &#150;09):</u></b></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><p align="justify">This substitutes the earlier hypothecation agreement on consumer Goods, 
      viz. S-9. This can be used for all advances where S-9 was used earlier.</p></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><b><u>cxlix) Hypothecation of Vehicle Agreement (SD-10):</u></b></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><p align="justify">This substitutes the earlier Hypothecation of Vehicle Agreement S-10. 
      This can be used for all vehicle loans and those for which S-10 was used 
      earlier.</p></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><u><b>cl) Housing Loan Agreement (SD-11):</b></u></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><p align="justify">This is the agreement meant for housing loan/Home Loan Scheme introduced 
      vide Instruction Circular No.6073 dated 16-08-2000. In this regard it may 
      be noted that mortgage of the house/flat has to be effected separately and 
      this agreement contains only the covenants with regard to the loan and no 
      security is created by this Deed. Mortgage has to be essentially created 
      separately.</p></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><b><u>cli) Mortgage Deed (Agricultural Advances) (SD-12):</u></b></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><p align="justify">This is a new deed introduced by Instruction Circular No. 5926 dated 31-08-1999. 
      This is to be used for all agricultural advances where simple mortgage is 
      stipulated as a security. Needless to add all formalities for creation of 
      a simple mortgage has to be complied with. In those States where the Agricultural 
      Credit Act permits creation of registered mortgage on the agricultural land 
      through a simplified procedure of registration of charge with Registrar 
      of Assurances, through the system stipulated therein, the same may be followed. </p>
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><b><u>clii) Simple Loan Agreement (SD-13)</u></b></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><p align="justify">This substitutes the earlier Simple Loan Agreement, viz. S-13. This is 
      meant for only agricultural advances where there is no direct/indirect security 
      is available to the Bank.</p></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><b><u>14. Simple Mortgage Deed (By Borrower) (SD-14)</u></b></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><p align="justify">This deed is meant for creation of simple mortgage for <b>advances other 
      than for Agricultural Advances..</b> This is a revised version of S-12 A. 
      This contains provisions for running accounts as well as for loans. All 
      formalities prescribed for simple mortgage are to be complied with including 
      registration of the Deed with the Sub-Registry in accordance with the procedure 
      prescribed for creation of simple mortgage.</p></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><b><u>15. Simple Mortgage Deed (By guarantor) (SD-15):</u></b></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><p align="justify">This deed is for creation of simple registered mortgage in respect of 
      advances where the mortgage property belongs to the third party (other than 
      the Borrower). Coupled with the mortgage created, third party personal guarantee 
      has also to be obtained in the said situation. This draft also has to be 
      typed out in non-judicial stamp paper and duly executed and duly registered 
      with the Sub-Registry in accordance with the procedure prescribed for creation 
      of simple mortgage.</p></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr> 
    <td><u><b>cliii) Pledge Agreement of Securities (SD-16):</b></u></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><p align="justify">This deed is meant for creation of pledge in respect of securities viz. 
      National Savings Certificates, Government Bonds, units, shares in the physical 
      form, etc.</p></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><b><u>cliv) Letter of Hypothecation of Bills (SD-17):</u></b></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><p align="justify">This deed is meant for hypothecation of Bills covered by DBP/FDBP/UDBP/FUDBP 
      . </p></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><u><b>clv) General Term Loan Agreement (SD-18):</b></u></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><p align="justify">This deed is a new document being introduced and to be obtained wherever 
      term loans are sanctioned. This document contains only personal covenants/undertakings 
      with regard to the loan transaction, viz. loan amount, details of disbursement, 
      instalments, repayment, default etc. and this is not a charging document. 
      Accordingly, depending upon the nature of security stipulated, separate 
      charging document has to be obtained. Please note that in the document, 
      the amount of instalment and number of instalments have to be clearly stated. 
      Also remember to score off the portions not applicable and the executants 
      to put their full signature in the cancelled portion.</p></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><b><u>19.Term Loan Agreement (Hypothecation of Movables) (SD-19):</u></b></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td>
      <p align="justify">This is a new document being introduced. This document is meant for Term 
        Loans either for purchase /acquisition of movable assets viz. Machinery 
        or capital goods or against such existing movable security. This document 
        is also to be used for DPGL facility sanctioned for purchase of machinery 
        or such other capital goods.<br>
      </p>
      <p align="justify">(This document should not be used for term loans for purchase of vehicles, 
        consumer durables for which separate documents are prescribed). This itself 
        is a charging document and hence no separate charging document is necessary. 
        Please remember to strike out whichever is not applicable if in a particular 
        account only newly purchased articles purchased out of our present loan 
        are charged or if existing machinery / assets only are charged. If both 
        i.e. newly purchased items as well as existing articles are available 
        as security to the Bank, both should be retained. Again please note to 
        fill in the schedules properly. In Schedule A (1) the assets/articles 
        procured out of present loan and in Schedule A (2) the existing plant 
        &amp; Machinery and other assets are to be stated depending upon the sanction 
        terms and securities in each case. Schedule B (1) is for Term Loan and 
        B (2) is for DPGL. </p>
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><b><u>clvi) COMPOSITE HYPOTHECATION DEED (SD-20):</u></b></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td>
     <p align="justify">This document is meant for a package of advance in the form of working 
        capital facility. This document is a comprehensive charging document on 
        the entire movable assets including Plant &amp; Machinery, stock, Book 
        Debts and all other current assets of the Borrower which are commonly 
        available for working capital facilities. This document can be ideally 
        obtained where working capital facility against stock/Book debts/current 
        assets along with Term Loan for Machinery is sanctioned or where Machinery 
        is stipulated as collateral security for the working capital facility. 
      </p>
    <p align="justify">However please note the following documents are to be taken separately 
        for the facilities as given hereunder: For Term Loans or DPGL, separate 
        General Term Loan Agreement for covering the covenants with regard to 
        loan transaction, separate D.P.Note and Letter of continuity for all running 
        facilities such as C.C. (hyp), Packing Credit, Bill Purchase, L/C limit 
        etc. and separate L/C applications for Import/Inland and Counter-indemnity 
        for Letters of Guarantee. </p>
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><b><u>SUPPLEMENTARY DEEDS :</u></b></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td>Four new supplementary Deeds are being introduced:</td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr> 
    <td width="4%">clvii)</td>
    <td width="96%">Supplementary SD-03</td>
  </tr>
  <tr> 
    <td width="4%">clviii)</td>
    <td width="96%">Supplementary SD-05</td>
  </tr>
  <tr> 
    <td width="4%">clix)</td>
    <td width="96%">Supplementary SD-06</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td width="4%">clx)</td>
    <td width="96%">Supplementary SD-20</td>
  </tr>
</table>
<p><br>
</p>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><p align="justify">These supplementary hypothecation agreements are primarily meant for those 
      states where ad valorem stamp duty is payable on Hypothecation Agreements. 
      These supplementary Deeds create additional charge over the security for 
      the additional/enhanced portion of the limit sanctioned. Accordingly these 
      would attract stamp duty only for those portion of the limit. Please further 
      note this deeds are the first supplemental deeds and if subsequent supplementals 
      are required, these deeds have to be suitably modified, in consultation 
      with the local lawyer.</p></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>
<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td><b>D.P. Notes &amp; D.B.C.&#146;s</b>: Please refer to Part I of this 
      chapter.</td>
  </tr>
